# Backend business rules

All rules below are enforced in code. Do not change behavior without updating this file and the implementation together.

---

## Events

### Event
- **Create**: User ID required (from auth). Name required, max 256 chars. `imageURL` and `location_link` must be valid URLs if provided. At least one event type required; type IDs must exist, be active, and have no duplicates. Defaults: `active=true`, `is_paid=false`, `is_online=false`. Protected on create: `id`, `created_at`, `created_by`, `deleted` are set by system.
- **Update**: User ID required. Cannot update a deleted event. Protected fields (stripped if sent): `id`, `created_at`, `created_by`, `deleted`. Name max 256 chars if provided. `active`, `is_paid`, `is_online` must be boolean if provided. If `type_ids` provided, same validation as create.
- **Delete**: Soft delete only. Must call validate-deletion first; deletion allowed only if event exists and is not already deleted. On delete: event `deleted=true`; all tickets for event set `active=false`, `deleted=true` and inventory `available_quantity=0`, metadata `event_deleted=true`; active user tickets set `status=CANCELLED`, `cancellation_reason=EVENT_CANCELLED`; stands/schedules set `active=false`, `deleted=true`; PENDING invitations set `status=CANCELLED`, `cancellation_reason=EVENT_CANCELLED`.

### Event type
- **Create**: User ID required. Name required, max 256 chars. `active` must be boolean. Name must be unique (case-insensitive) among non-deleted event types.
- **Update**: User ID required. If name is changed, new name must be unique among event types.
- **Delete**: Soft delete (no pre-check in code for “in use by events” — TODO in code).

---

## Products / Tickets (events function)

Tickets are products with `type=TICKET`, `parent_type=EVENT`. Rules below apply to products (including tickets) unless stated otherwise.

### Product (create)
- User ID required. Name required, max 256 chars. Description required. `active` and `is_free` must be boolean if provided. Default `active=true`.
- If `is_free` then `value` is forced to 0; else `value` must be number/bigint and > 0.
- `quantity` if provided: positive integer. `max_per_user` if provided: positive integer.
- Product is created with inventory; inventory ID pattern `TICKET_<productId>` for tickets.

### Product (update)
- User ID required. Product must exist and belong to parent; cannot update a deleted product. Protected fields (stripped): `id`, `parentId`, `created_at`, `deleted`. Name max 256 chars if provided. `active` must be boolean if provided. Inventory is updated when product quantity or value changes (e.g. `available_quantity = quantity - reserved_quantity`).

### Product (delete)
- Product must exist and belong to parent. Soft delete: product and inventory deactivated in a transaction.

### Product (get by id / availability / inventory)
- Product must exist and `product.parent_id` must match request parent (event id for tickets).

### Product quantity update
- User ID required. Quantity must be a positive integer. Product must exist and belong to parent. Inventory total and available quantities updated accordingly.

---

## Stands

- **Create**: User ID required. Event must exist. Name required, max 256 chars. `base_price` must be >= 0. `location.coordinates.x` and `location.coordinates.y` must be numbers. Initial `status=available`, `deleted=false`.
- **Update**: User ID and event required. Stand must exist. Name max 256 if provided. Coordinates validated if provided. `base_price` if provided must be >= 0. `status` if provided must be `available` or `maintenance`.
- **Delete**: Soft delete: `deleted=true`. Event and stand must exist.

---

## Schedules

- **Create**: Event must exist. If `parent_id` provided: parent schedule must exist and belong to same event; child schedule must be within parent date/time and include parent exclusions (ScheduleManager.validateSchedule). Dates: `YYYY-MM-DD`. Times: `HH:mm` (e.g. 09:00). End date must be >= start date; on same day, start time must be before end time. No overlap with other non-cancelled, non-completed schedules for the event (ScheduleManager.checkScheduleOverlaps).
- **Update**: Same validations as create for the resulting schedule; parent must belong to event; no overlaps (excluding current schedule when updating).
- **Delete**: Schedule must exist and belong to event. Cannot delete if it has child schedules (`parent_id` pointing to it).

---

## Invitations

### Constants (INVITATION_RULES)
- `EXPIRATION_DAYS`: 7. `MAX_INVITATIONS_PER_HOUR` and `MAX_INVITATIONS_PER_DAY`: 1000 each. Email: regex `^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$`. Phone (SMS/WhatsApp): `^\+?[\d\s-]{10,}$`.

### Create
- User ID required. Event must exist. Each `ticket_id` must be a product that exists and has `parent_id = eventId`. `type` must be one of: LINK. `destination_type` must be one of: EMAIL, SMS, WHATSAPP, USER_ID. Destination validated by type: EMAIL → email regex; SMS/WHATSAPP → phone regex. Rate limits: per inviter, max INVITATION_RULES.MAX_INVITATIONS_PER_HOUR in last hour and MAX_INVITATIONS_PER_DAY in last 24h. If `expires_at` provided it must be valid date and in the future; else default 7 days from now. Initial `status=PENDING`.

### Update
- Invitation must exist and `invitation.event_id` must match request `eventId`. Ticket IDs if provided must exist and belong to event. Type/destination_type/destination/expires_at validated same as create when provided. Expires_at must be in the future if provided. Token is regenerated on update.

### Status transitions (updateInvitationStatusWithValidation)
- PENDING → ACCEPTED, DECLINED, EXPIRED, CANCELLED.
- ACCEPTED → CANCELLED.
- DECLINED, EXPIRED, CANCELLED → no transitions.

### Validate invitation (get by id / get products — public)
- Invitation must exist. If `expires_at` is in the past and status is PENDING: status is set to EXPIRED and "Invitation has expired" is thrown. Otherwise invitation is valid for the request.

### Decline (public)
- Invitation must exist. Only PENDING invitations can be declined. Status set to DECLINED; optional message stored in metadata.

### Trigger (on payment APPROVED)
- If order has `metadata.invitation_id`, invitation is updated to ACCEPTED only if current status is not already ACCEPTED and not DECLINED (DECLINED must not be overwritten to ACCEPTED). Metadata can include `order_id`, `payment_id`, `message`.

---

## Attendees

- **Create**: User ID required. Event must exist. `user_product_id` must be a user product that exists and has `user_id = req.user.id`. If `invitation_id` provided, invitation must exist and `invitation.event_id = eventId`. Initial `status=REGISTERED`.
- **Status update**: Allowed transitions: REGISTERED → CHECKED_IN, CANCELLED, NO_SHOW. CHECKED_IN, CANCELLED, NO_SHOW → no transitions. On transition to CHECKED_IN, `check_in_time` is set.

