## User tickets / User products (events)

User tickets are user products in event context. Create/get/list/update status/update additional_data delegate to shared UserProductController.

### Update additional data by invitation (public route)
- If request has no auth user, `req.user.id` is set from invitation’s `inviter_id` (invitation must exist). Then same rules as updateUserProductAdditionalData: user product must exist, additional_data required in body, user must own the user product (or be the inviter when called via invitation flow).

### User product status transitions (shared)
- ACTIVE → USED, EXPIRED, CANCELLED.
- USED → REFUNDED.
- CANCELLED → REFUNDED.
- EXPIRED, REFUNDED → no transitions.

### User product additional data
- User ID required. User product must exist. Request must contain `additional_data` (object). Merged with existing additional_data.

